	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ok just a quick summary here of the posts above. <BR>
<BR>
One, this item is dropped by the Foreman in Sol A. <BR>
<BR>
Two, the Foreman is a Flame Goblin around lv 25. He can be anywhere from lv 24 to 26. He hits really hard though :)<BR>
<BR>
Three, The room itself is not hard to hold if you can break in you can do this at lv 21 even in a FULL group. However, if even one runner gets away then parties of lv 30 and higher start getting smashed really quick. Corpse recivery can be very hard too. <BR>
<BR>
Four, Spawn time on the Foreman is very chaotic. The spawn itself is around 20 mins. But it is random whether he or his place holder spawns. Average is one foreman every 3 spawns. I have personally done an 18 hour camp without seing one Foreman though. As I said very Chaotic.<BR>
<BR>
Five, his common drop is the Tunic. Great item in and of itself. The Scimitar is his rare and I do mean rare. Some people have lucked out on it but do not ever go into this camp EXPECTING to get a scimitar. You will most likely only get Tunics. If a scimitar spawns consider yourself lucky. <BR>
<BR>
Six, the Scimitar is not a very good weapon for melee types. However, it is a Druids dream. This is beyond all doubt one of the best non Dragon/Plane weapons for Druids. I would say that the Silvery Scimitar is much better but it is also much harder to get than the Obsidian.<BR>
<BR>
Seven, Obsidian Scimitars sell for 600 to 800 pp average if they are not trade only. Worth every penny to a Druid.<BR>
<BR>
Well that is my 2 cp. <BR>
<BR>
BTW, as of 1/14/00 I have one for sale on Erollisi Marr. I want coin on this one as I am trying to finance an Ebony Blade, 700 PP is my asking price. Course if you want to trade an ebony for this I will gladly oblige ya! :) Contact me in game if interested.<BR>
Vanidar Moonwhisper,<BR>
Ranger of Erollisi Marr
				</font>
			</td>

