	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Just thought I'd throw in my two cents:<BR>
<BR>
(1) Some people have had more luck in getting this item than others.  For those people, good show, congratulations, but please, please don't call us liars when we say that we had a devil of a time getting this thing.  I camped the foreman for a week and a half with friends, sitting in that smelly old room for hours at a stretch, it was a pain and a nightmare, but finally we obtained three of these, one for the druid and two for me (I'm a warrior, by the way.)  My experience was that the foreman is a VERY erratic spawn, and far more often than not has the tunic rather than the scimitar.  Your mileage may vary, of course.<BR>
<BR>
(2) While there are some who doubt the value of this weapon for a warrior, I respectfully disagree.  I believe, from experience, that this is an excellent weapon for a warrior. (And it goes without saying that it's incredible for druids!) The agility bonus is very nice, and the ratio on this weapon is 3.9, which is very good.  Please note, for comparison, that the ratio on the much-touted Bladed Thulian Claw is 3.8, at least according to the good folks over at EQ'Lizer.  And yes, I'm well aware that the silvery war axe has a better ratio, at 3.67.  I wield a pair of these, and thanks to the agility bonus, I'm not the slightest bit sorry that I don't use a claw or silvery war axe.  <BR>
<BR>
(3) Finally, dual wielding scimitars looks very cool, in my opinion.  If that sort of thing is important to you (and it is to me, for certain) and you don't want to look like every other warrior or ranger out there, give these a go. (Yes, incidentally, I am in fact the kind of guy who wouldn't take a rubicite breastplate because it would clash with his crafted, why do you ask? =) )<BR>
<BR>
For all those who are searching for one of these, I wish you the best (and better luck than I had!).  You won't regret the effort.<BR>
<BR>
Cheers, <BR>
<BR>
Fitzwillow Fairbrass<BR>
32d rank Warrior and Deputy of the Vale<BR>
Quellious Server
				</font>
			</td>

